Neat solution, thought I'd save it. The important part is <code>type: "head"</code>, which only returns the headers received from the request.
<code>
$.ajax({ type: 'HEAD', url: '/path/to/a/file.pdf', complete: function (e,d) { if ( e.status == 404 ) { alert("file does not exist") } } });
</code>
